column1: #Text=travertine - compact calcium carbonate deposit, often banded, precipitated from spring, river or lake water. cf. tufa.
#Text=tube - a cave passage of smooth surface, and elliptical or nearly circular in cross-section.
#Text=tufa - spongy or vesicular calcium carbonate deposited from spring, river or lake waters.
#Text=twilight zone - the part of a cave to which daylight penetrates.
#Text=uvala - a complex dosed depression with several lesser depressions within its rim.
#Text=vadose zone - the zone where voids in the rock are partly filled with air and through which water descends under gravity.
#Text=vauclusian spring - a spring rising up a deep, steeply inclined, waterfilled passage into a small surface pool.
#Text=vermiculation - pattern of thin, worm-shaped coatings of day or silt on cave surfaces.
#Text=water table - the surface between phreatic water, which completely fills voids in the rock, and ground air, which partially fills higher voids.
#Text=water tracing - determination of water connection between points of stream disappearance or of soil water seepage and points of reappearance on the surface or underground.
#Text=well - a deep rounded hole in a cave floor or on the surface in karst.
